The paper discusses a machine learning algorithm for imitation learning, which involves learning how to behave in an environment by mimicking expert demonstrations. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm is designed to work in large, high-dimensional environments, which suggests that it may be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions that the algorithm can be applied to continuous environments, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) for perception.
